TITLE: Multi-Select Dynamic Dropdown Property in Typescript
DESCRIPTION: Defines a property that allows multiple selections from dynamically loaded options.  The `refreshers` array lists properties whose changes trigger option updates. The `options` property takes an async function returning options with `label` and `value`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/activepieces/activepieces/blob/main/docs/developers/piece-reference/properties.mdx#_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
Property.MultiSelectDropdown({
  displayName: 'Options',
  description: 'Select one or more options',
  required: true,
  refreshers: ['auth'],
  options: async ({ auth }) => {
    if (!auth) {
      return {
        disabled: true,
      };
    }
    return {
      options: [
        {
          label: 'Option One',
          value: '1',
        },
        {
          label: 'Option Two',
          value: '2',
        },
      ],
    };
  },
});
```

