TITLE: Storing a Value in Persistent Storage (Put)
DESCRIPTION: Stores a value associated with a given key in the Activepieces persistent storage. The `ctx.store.put` method is used to store the value. The scope can be either at flow or project level. The example demonstrates storing a string value with 'KEY' as the key in the project scope.
SOURCE: https://github.com/activepieces/activepieces/blob/main/docs/developers/piece-reference/persistent-storage.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
ctx.store.put('KEY', 'VALUE', StoreScope.PROJECT);
```

