TITLE: Stopping Flow without Response - Typescript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to stop the execution of a flow without sending a response back to the webhook trigger in Activepieces. It uses the `context.run.stop()` method without any arguments, effectively terminating the flow without any additional output.
SOURCE: https://github.com/activepieces/activepieces/blob/main/docs/developers/piece-reference/flow-control.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
context.run.stop();
```

