TITLE: Generating JWT with jsonwebtoken in Node.js
DESCRIPTION: This Node.js snippet demonstrates how to generate a JWT token using the `jsonwebtoken` library. It sets the payload claims, including user ID, project ID, role, and expiration time. The token is signed using the RS256 algorithm and a private key (ACTIVEPIECES_SIGNING_KEY), and the signing key ID (`kid`) is included in the header.
SOURCE: https://github.com/activepieces/activepieces/blob/main/docs/embedding/provision-users.mdx#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');

// JWT NumericDates specified in seconds:
const currentTime = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);
let token = jwt.sign(
  {
    version: "v3",
    externalUserId: "user_id",
    externalProjectId: "user_project_id",
    firstName: "John",
    lastName: "Doe",
    role: "EDITOR",
    piecesFilterType: "NONE",
    exp: currentTime + (60 * 60), // 1 hour from now
  },
  process.env.ACTIVEPIECES_SIGNING_KEY,
  {
    algorithm: "RS256",
    header: {
      kid: signingKeyID, // Include the "kid" in the header
    },
  }
);
```

