TITLE: Username and Password Authentication with Validation
DESCRIPTION: Defines a `BasicAuth` authentication method for collecting username and password credentials. Includes optional validation to ensure that credentials have been passed. Returns a validation result with a boolean 'valid' and an optional error message.
SOURCE: https://github.com/activepieces/activepieces/blob/main/docs/developers/piece-reference/authentication.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
PieceAuth.BasicAuth({
    displayName: 'Credentials',
    description: 'Enter your username and password',
    required: true,
    username: {
        displayName: 'Username',
        description: 'Enter your username',
    },
    password: {
        displayName: 'Password',
        description: 'Enter your password',
    },
    // Optional Validation
    validate: async ({auth}) => {
        if(auth){
            return {
                valid: true,
            }
        }
        return {
            valid: false,
            error: 'Invalid Api Key'
        }
    }
})
```

