TITLE: Dictionary Property Definition in Typescript
DESCRIPTION: Defines a property that collects key-value pairs from the user. It's also referred to as Object property. It includes options for display name, description, whether the field is required, and a default value (as a JSON object).
SOURCE: https://github.com/activepieces/activepieces/blob/main/docs/developers/piece-reference/properties.mdx#_snippet_9

